---
import { SITE_TITLE } from '../config/site';
import SiteLayout from '../layouts/SiteLayout.astro';
---

<SiteLayout
  title={`${SITE_TITLE} Stats`}
  description="Review your local bang usage, hot streaks, and recent search patterns."
  currentPath="/stats"
  pageScript="stats"
>
  <section class="grid gap-4 lg:grid-cols-[minmax(0,0.92fr)_minmax(300px,0.68fr)]">
    <div class="card overflow-hidden p-0">
      <div
        class="relative overflow-hidden bg-linear-to-br from-slate-950 via-slate-900 to-blue-950 px-5 py-6 text-white sm:px-6 sm:py-7"
      >
        <div class="absolute right-[-64px] top-[-72px] h-40 w-40 rounded-full bg-blue-400/18 blur-3xl"></div>
        <div class="absolute bottom-[-48px] left-[18%] h-28 w-28 rounded-full bg-cyan-300/12 blur-3xl"></div>
        <div class="relative">
          <p class="text-xs font-700 uppercase tracking-[0.24em] text-blue-100/78">Local analytics</p>
          <h1
            class="mt-3 max-w-[12ch] font-display text-[2.35rem] font-800 leading-[0.95] tracking-[-0.05em] sm:text-[3rem]"
          >
            See which bangs you actually use
          </h1>
          <p class="mt-4 max-w-[60ch] text-sm leading-7 text-blue-50/82 sm:text-[0.98rem]">
            Stats live in your browser. Recent activity counts more than stale history, frequent
            bangs climb faster, and repeated query patterns help the suggestion engine rank what
            you are likely reaching for next.
          </p>
          <div class="mt-5 flex flex-wrap gap-2 text-xs font-700 uppercase tracking-[0.16em]">
            <span class="rounded-full border border-white/12 bg-white/8 px-3 py-2 text-blue-50/86">
              Time decay
            </span>
            <span class="rounded-full border border-white/12 bg-white/8 px-3 py-2 text-blue-50/86">
              Frequency
            </span>
            <span class="rounded-full border border-white/12 bg-white/8 px-3 py-2 text-blue-50/86">
              Query similarity
            </span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <aside class="card p-5 sm:p-6">
      <p class="text-xs font-700 uppercase tracking-[0.24em] text-primary-700">How ranking works</p>
      <div class="mt-4 grid gap-3">
        <div class="rounded-[22px] bg-bg-soft p-4">
          <p class="text-sm font-700 text-text">Recency stays hot</p>
          <p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-6 text-text-secondary">
            New activity gets the strongest weight, then decays over time so old habits stop
            dominating.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="rounded-[22px] bg-bg-soft p-4">
          <p class="text-sm font-700 text-text">Frequency builds momentum</p>
          <p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-6 text-text-secondary">
            Repeated use compounds a bang&apos;s score, which makes your common shortcuts surface
            earlier.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="rounded-[22px] bg-bg-soft p-4">
          <p class="text-sm font-700 text-text">Queries leave a trail</p>
          <p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-6 text-text-secondary">
            Recent search phrases are kept locally and used to nudge matching bang suggestions.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </aside>
  </section>

  <section id="stats-empty" class="card mt-4 hidden p-6 sm:p-7">
    <div
      class="rounded-[28px] border border-dashed border-white/70 bg-bg-soft px-5 py-8 text-center dark:border-white/12"
    >
      <p class="text-xs font-700 uppercase tracking-[0.22em] text-primary-700">No activity yet</p>
      <h2
        class="mt-3 font-display text-[2rem] font-800 tracking-[-0.04em] text-text sm:text-[2.35rem]"
      >
        Use a few bangs, then come back
      </h2>
      <p class="mx-auto mt-3 max-w-[50ch] text-sm leading-7 text-text-secondary">
        Run searches like <code>!gh astro</code>, <code>!mdn fetch</code>, or
        <code>!w saturn</code> and this page will start visualizing what you use most.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="stats-dashboard" class="mt-4 grid gap-4">
    <div id="stats-summary" class="grid gap-4 sm:grid-cols-2 xl:grid-cols-4"></div>

    <section class="card overflow-hidden p-5 sm:p-6">
      <div class="flex flex-wrap items-end justify-between gap-4">
        <div>
          <p class="text-xs font-700 uppercase tracking-[0.24em] text-primary-700">Weekly rhythm</p>
          <h2 class="section-title mt-2">When you search most</h2>
        </div>
        <p class="text-xs text-text-secondary">Local time, device-only history</p>
      </div>
      <p id="stats-heatmap-summary" class="mt-2 max-w-[72ch] text-sm leading-7 text-text-secondary"></p>
      <div class="mt-5 overflow-x-auto pb-1">
        <div class="min-w-[780px]">
          <div class="mb-2 flex items-center gap-2 sm:gap-3">
            <div class="w-11 shrink-0"></div>
            <div class="grid flex-1 gap-1.5" style="grid-template-columns: repeat(24, minmax(0, 1fr));">
              {
                Array.from({ length: 24 }, (_, hour) => (
                  <div class="text-center text-[10px] font-700 uppercase tracking-[0.14em] text-text-muted">
                    {hour % 6 === 0 ? `${hour}` : ''}
                  </div>
                ))
              }
            </div>
          </div>
          <div
            id="stats-heatmap-grid"
            class="grid gap-1.5"
            role="grid"
            aria-label="Search activity heatmap by day of week and hour"
          ></div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="mt-4 flex flex-wrap items-center gap-3 text-xs text-text-secondary">
        <span>Lower activity</span>
        <div class="flex items-center gap-1.5">
          <span class="h-3 w-5 rounded-full border border-white/65 bg-[rgba(59,130,246,0.08)] dark:border-white/8"></span>
          <span class="h-3 w-5 rounded-full border border-white/65 bg-[rgba(59,130,246,0.28)] dark:border-white/8"></span>
          <span class="h-3 w-5 rounded-full border border-white/65 bg-[rgba(59,130,246,0.52)] dark:border-white/8"></span>
          <span class="h-3 w-5 rounded-full border border-white/65 bg-[rgba(34,211,238,0.86)] dark:border-white/8"></span>
        </div>
        <span>Higher activity</span>
      </div>
    </section>

    <div class="grid gap-4 xl:grid-cols-[minmax(0,1.2fr)_minmax(300px,0.8fr)]">
      <section class="card p-5 sm:p-6">
        <div class="flex items-end justify-between gap-4">
          <div>
            <p class="text-xs font-700 uppercase tracking-[0.24em] text-primary-700">Leaderboard</p>
            <h2 class="section-title mt-2">Top bangs by live score</h2>
          </div>
          <p class="text-xs text-text-secondary">Decayed score + use count</p>
        </div>
        <div id="stats-top-list" class="mt-5 grid gap-3"></div>
      </section>

      <section class="card p-5 sm:p-6">
        <p class="text-xs font-700 uppercase tracking-[0.24em] text-primary-700">Recent activity</p>
        <h2 class="section-title mt-2">Freshest bangs</h2>
        <div id="stats-recent-list" class="mt-5 grid gap-3"></div>
      </section>
    </div>

    <div class="grid gap-4 lg:grid-cols-[minmax(0,0.92fr)_minmax(280px,0.68fr)]">
      <section class="card p-5 sm:p-6">
        <p class="text-xs font-700 uppercase tracking-[0.24em] text-primary-700">Query memory</p>
        <h2 class="section-title mt-2">Search patterns the ranker can see</h2>
        <p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-7 text-text-secondary">
          These recent local query samples are what power the query-similarity boost.
        </p>
        <div id="stats-query-groups" class="mt-5 grid gap-3"></div>
      </section>

      <section class="card p-5 sm:p-6">
        <p class="text-xs font-700 uppercase tracking-[0.24em] text-primary-700">Device scope</p>
        <h2 class="section-title mt-2">What gets stored</h2>
        <div class="mt-4 grid gap-3 text-sm leading-6 text-text-secondary">
          <div class="rounded-[20px] bg-bg-soft p-4">
            Bang trigger, total uses, recency-weighted score, last-used time, and a few recent
            search phrases.
          </div>
          <div class="rounded-[20px] bg-bg-soft p-4">
            Everything stays local in your browser storage. There is no account sync or remote
            analytics endpoint behind this page.
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>
    </div>
  </section>
</SiteLayout>
